<org.eclipse.epf.uma:ArtifactDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmi:id="_1C0U1dnmEdmO6L4XMImrsA" name="rup_supplementary_specification,{B16C2941-791C-44E6-B353-354109B5C9DE}" guid="_1C0U1dnmEdmO6L4XMImrsA" changeDate="2005-11-15T17:13:19.475-0800" version="7.1.0">
  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The Supplementary Specifications are an important complement to the &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../core.base_rup/workproducts/rup_usecase_model_EF15E534.html&quot; guid=&quot;{9C66F2EC-EDEB-4369-9AFB-04B9E7CBCB8E}&quot;>Use-Case&#xD;
    Model&lt;/a>, because together they capture all &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../core.base_rup/guidances/concepts/requirements_62E28784.html&quot; guid=&quot;4.582668643506599E-305&quot;>software requirements&#xD;
    (functional and nonfunctional)&lt;/a> that need to be described to serve as a complete &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../core.base_rup/workproducts/rup_software_requirements_specification_934E66F.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;{BE8165DC-BAF2-4237-B27D-F2A037023364}&quot;>Software Requirements Specification&lt;/a>.&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
  <keyConsiderations>The Supplementary Specification captures all system-wide requirements, not just the non-functional ones.&amp;nbsp; A common&#xD;
misconception is that all functional requirements reside in the &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
href=&quot;./../../core.base_rup/workproducts/rup_usecase_A5D30E62.html&quot; guid=&quot;{B1526BC5-E346-42CB-A08A-3C0D7F382407}&quot;>Use&#xD;
Case&lt;/a>&amp;nbsp;work products and all non-functional requirements reside in the Supplemental Specification work product. This&#xD;
is inaccurate as some functional requirements apply to the system as a whole (such as a requirement for online help).&#xD;
Similarly, some non-functional requirements only apply to a particular use case (or flow within a use case), in which case&#xD;
the requirement should be attached to the use case, otherwise the system will be over-engineered.</keyConsiderations>
  <purpose>&lt;a id=&quot;Top&quot; name=&quot;Top&quot;>&lt;/a>&lt;a id=&quot;XE_supplementary_specifications__artifact_definition&quot;&#xD;
name=&quot;XE_supplementary_specifications__artifact_definition&quot;>&lt;/a>&lt;a id=&quot;Purpose&quot; name=&quot;Purpose&quot;>&lt;/a> &#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The Supplementary Specifications capture the system requirements that are not readily captured in the use cases of the&#xD;
    use-case model. Such requirements include:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Legal and regulatory requirements, and application standards&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Quality attributes of the system to be built, including usability, reliability, performance, and supportability&#xD;
        requirements&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Other requirements such as those for operating systems and environments, compatibility with other software, and&#xD;
        design constraints&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></purpose>
  <briefOutline>&lt;p>&#xD;
    It is recommended that the Supplementary Specification be organized according the requirement categories.&amp;nbsp; For a&#xD;
    description of a categorization approach using the &quot;FURPS+&quot; acronym, see &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithType&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../core.base_rup/guidances/concepts/requirements_62E28784.html&quot; guid=&quot;4.582668643506599E-305&quot;>Concept:&#xD;
    Requirements&lt;/a>.&#xD;
&lt;/p></briefOutline>
  <representationOptions>&lt;a id=&quot;Tailoring&quot; name=&quot;Tailoring&quot;>&lt;/a> &#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The kinds of supplementary requirements vary widely between projects, so tailoring should be applied to define sections&#xD;
    applicable to your project.&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;/p></representationOptions>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:ArtifactDescription>
